TY  - JOUR
TI  - The Once But Not Twice Differentiability of the Policy Function
AU  - Araujo, A.
AB  - [It is shown that an increasing policy function that is the solution of a C<sup>2</sup> dynamic programming problem is always C<sup>1</sup>. This implies that the value function is C<sup>2</sup>. Examples are given to show that the policy function might not be twice differentiable and therefore the value might not be three times differentiable, even if the program is C<sup>3</sup>.]
